    ‚ąá r‚Üź{ucs}Do sql
   ‚ćĚ Execute SQL statement. If SELECT, return result.
      :If 0=‚éēNC'ucs' ‚čĄ ucs‚Üź0 ‚čĄ :EndIf  ‚ćĚ Unicode convert these columns
      r‚ÜźCatch SQA.Do db sql
      :If 0=‚äÉr
          :If 5=‚ČĘr
              r‚Üź3 1‚äÉr
              (ucs/r)‚ÜźFromUTF8¬®ucs/r
          :EndIf
      :ElseIf '08S01'‚Č°‚äÉ2‚äÉr           ‚ćĚ SQL Server has gone away, attempt to reconnect
                                     ‚ćĚ ‚äÉ2‚äÉ fail safe in case non-nested inner structure
          SQA.Close db
          Connect ##.GetEnv¬®'SQL_DATABASE' 'SQL_PASSWORD' 'SQL_USER'
          r‚Üźucs Do sql
      :Else
          ‚éēSIGNAL‚äā('EN' 500)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'(Print 3‚äÉr))   ‚ćĚ Other SQL error
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ćĚ ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ CRUD functions ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
    ‚ćĚ Work around 16384-char SQA.Do result-buffer using low-level Prepare/Exec/Fetch
    ‚ćĚ with explicit SQAPL result-column type annotations
    ‚ćĚ Each CRUD function takes a single options namespace and returns the rows affected by the statement

      TypesFor‚Üź{
     ‚ćĚ ‚ćļ: table name. ‚ćĶ: column names.
     ‚ćĚ ‚Üź: SQAPL type strings (with leading '<') for those columns in ‚ćĶ's order.
          ti‚Üź##.GLOBAL.tables‚ć≥‚äā‚ćļ
          ti>‚ČĘ##.GLOBAL.tables:‚éēSIGNAL‚äā('EN' 500)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'('Unknown table: ',‚ćļ))
          allcols‚Üźti‚äÉ##.GLOBAL.columns
          alltypes‚Üźti‚äÉ##.GLOBAL.type_sqapl
          ci‚Üźallcols‚ć≥‚ćĶ
          ‚ą®/bad‚Üźci>‚ČĘallcols:‚éēSIGNAL‚äā('EN' 500)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'('Unknown columns: ',‚ćēbad/‚ćĶ))
          alltypes[ci]
      }

    WrapColNames‚Üź(1‚Üď‚ąä){',`',‚ćĶ,'`'}¬®              ‚ćĚ `a`,`b`
    WrapValueTypes‚Üź(1‚Üď‚ąä){',:',‚ćĶ,':'}¬®            ‚ćĚ :<C10:,:<I:
    WrapResultTypes‚Üź{':>',(1‚Üď‚ąä','‚ąė,¬®1‚Üď¬®‚ćĶ),':'}   ‚ćĚ :>C10,I:   ‚ćĚ FIXME if we store types without < don't need 1‚Üď¬®

      Fetch‚Üź{
     ‚ćĚ ‚ćļ (optional): nested vector of bind values. ‚ć¨ means no binds.
     ‚ćĚ ‚ćĶ: annotated SQL statement.
     ‚ćĚ ‚Üź: result matrix (2‚äÉ of SQA.Fetch), or ‚éēSIGNAL on failure.
          ‚ćļ‚Üź‚ć¨ ‚čĄ values‚Üź‚ćļ ‚čĄ sql‚Üź‚ćĶ
          cur‚Üź2‚äÉSQA.CursorName db
          Fail‚Üź{_‚ÜźSQA.Close cur ‚čĄ ‚éēSIGNAL‚äā('EN' 500)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'(3‚äÉ‚ćĶ))}
          0‚Č†‚äÉp‚ÜźSQA.Prepare cur sql:Fail p
          e‚Üź{0=‚ČĘvalues:SQA.Exec cur ‚čĄ SQA.Exec cur‚äā‚ćõ,values}‚ć¨
          0‚Č†‚äÉe:Fail e
          0‚Č†‚äÉf‚Üź1 SQA.Fetch cur:Fail f
          _‚ÜźSQA.Close cur
          2‚äÉf
      }

      ExecBind‚Üź{
     ‚ćĚ Like Fetch, but for statements that produce no result set.
          ‚ćļ‚Üź‚ć¨ ‚čĄ values‚Üź‚ćļ ‚čĄ sql‚Üź‚ćĶ
          cur‚Üź2‚äÉSQA.CursorName db
          Fail‚Üź{_‚ÜźSQA.Close cur ‚čĄ ‚éēSIGNAL‚äā('EN' 500)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'(3‚äÉ‚ćĶ))}
          0‚Č†‚äÉp‚ÜźSQA.Prepare cur sql:Fail p
          e‚Üź{0=‚ČĘvalues:SQA.Exec cur ‚čĄ SQA.Exec cur‚äā‚ćõ,values}‚ć¨
          0‚Č†‚äÉe:Fail ‚éē‚Üźe
          _‚ÜźSQA.Close cur
          0
      }

    ‚ćĚ Crud functions Select/Insert/Update/Delete take a single options namespace. Fields:
    ‚ćĚ   table     : table name (required)
    ‚ćĚ   columns   : insert / set / get columns (Select, Insert, Update)
    ‚ćĚ   values    : matrix of input tuples (Insert, Update)
    ‚ćĚ   where     : literal WHERE clause, without the 'WHERE' keyword (Select, Update, Delete)
    ‚ćĚ   returning : columns to return via RETURNING (Insert, Update)

      Select‚Üź{
     ‚ćĚ Returns matrix of rows, columns in `columns` order.
          (table where)‚Üź‚ćĶ ‚éēVGET('table')('where' '')
          columns‚Üź‚éēVGET‚äā('columns'(Columns table))
          return_types‚Üźtable TypesFor columns
          sql‚Üź'SELECT ',(WrapColNames columns),' FROM ',table,((0<‚ČĘwhere)/' WHERE '),where,' ',WrapResultTypes return_types
          ‚äÉFetch sql
      }
      
      Insert‚Üź{
     ‚ćĚ Empty cells in `values` become SQL NULLs. Returns matrix of inserted rows with "RETURNING".
          (table columns values returning)‚Üź‚ćĶ ‚éēVGET('table' '')('columns'‚ć¨)('values'‚ć¨)('returning'‚ć¨)
          insert_types‚Üźtable TypesFor columns
          return_types‚Üźtable TypesFor returning
          sql‚Üź'INSERT INTO ',table,' (',(WrapColNames columns),') VALUES (',(WrapValueTypes insert_types),') RETURNING ',(WrapColNames returning),' ',WrapResultTypes return_types
          nulls‚Üź(0‚ąä‚ćī)¬®values
          values[‚ćł(insert_types‚ąä‚äā'<S')(‚ąß‚ć§1)nulls]‚Üź‚äā19‚ćī''   ‚ćĚ datetime placeholder for nulls
          values[‚ćł(insert_types‚ąä‚äā'<I')(‚ąß‚ć§1)nulls]‚Üź0        ‚ćĚ integer placeholder for nulls
          (values nulls) Transact sql
      }

      Transact‚Üź{
          (values nulls)‚Üź‚ćļ ‚čĄ sql‚Üź‚ćĶ
          _‚ÜźDo'START TRANSACTION'
          0::‚éēSIGNAL ‚äā‚éēDMX.(('EN'EN)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'Message))‚ä£Do'ROLLBACK'
          ‚äÉ‚ć™‚ĆŅ(values,nulls)(Fetch‚ć§1)sql
      }

      Update‚Üź{
     ‚ćĚ Same `where` applied to every row of `values`. Returns matrix of
     ‚ćĚ affected rows projected through `returning`. MariaDB v10 does not support
     ‚ćĚ UPDATE...RETURNING, so the UPDATE and a follow-up SELECT are issued in
     ‚ćĚ a single transaction.
          (table columns values where returning)‚Üź‚ćĶ ‚éēVGET('table' '')('columns'‚ć¨)('values'‚ć¨)('where' '')('returning'‚ć¨)
          set_types‚Üźtable TypesFor columns
          return_types‚Üźtable TypesFor returning
          SetPair‚Üź{',`',‚ćļ,'`=:',‚ćĶ,':'}
          set_clause‚Üź1‚Üď‚ąäcolumns SetPair¬®set_types
          upd_sql‚Üź'UPDATE ',table,' SET ',set_clause,' WHERE ',where
          sel_sql‚Üź'SELECT ',(WrapColNames returning),' FROM ',table,' WHERE ',where,' ',WrapResultTypes return_types
          nulls‚Üź(0‚ąä‚ćī)¬®values
          values[‚ćł(set_types‚ąä‚äā'<S')(‚ąß‚ć§1)nulls]‚Üź‚äā19‚ćī''
          values[‚ćł(set_types‚ąä‚äā'<I')(‚ąß‚ć§1)nulls]‚Üź0
          _‚ÜźDo'START TRANSACTION'
          0::‚éēSIGNAL ‚äā‚éēDMX.(('EN'EN)('Vendor' 'DCMS')('Message'Message))‚ä£Do'ROLLBACK'
          _‚Üź(values,nulls)(ExecBind‚ć§1)upd_sql
          ‚äÉFetch sel_sql
      }

      Delete‚Üź{
          (table where)‚Üź‚ćĶ ‚éēVGET('table' '')('where' '')
          Do'DELETE FROM ',table,' WHERE ',where
      }

    Print‚Üź{1‚éēJSON 1‚Üď,(‚éēucs 13),30(‚Ćä‚ąė‚ČĘ‚ÜĎ‚äĘ)‚ćē‚ćĶ}

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźColumns table
